<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Chip boost for signal
processing speed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANNA KOCHAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An electronic chip that could significantly increase signal processing
speeds has been developed by Robomatix Technologies, writes Anna Kochan.
Tests to be completed by early summer on an initial production batch of 160
chips will prove whether Robomatix has succeeded where others have failed,
says Zami Aberman, president of the Israeli company.
He describes the Xium chip as massively parallel; it incorporates 1,024
processors. Simulations show a Xium chip could perform 1bn instructions per
second. It would function as a single chip or as part of a computer board.
If the tests prove successful, Robomatix plans to put the chip into
automated inspection systems. Its ability to perform real-time recognition
and processing of data could be useful in video-conferencing and air traffic
control systems.
Robomatix: Israel, 9729 986976.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>ILZ  Israel, Middle East.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P3674 Semiconductors and Related Devices.
</IN>
<XX>
