FT  13 MAY 94 / BBC journalists to hold strikes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BBC journalists have voted to stage a series of 24-hour strikes in a dispute
over pay and working conditions.
A large majority of members of the National Union of Journalists voted in
favour of a stoppage although fewer than half the 2,274 journalists took
part in the ballot.
Members of Bectu, the main broadcasting union, voted at the weekend for a
series of 24-hour strikes and threatened to disrupt outside sports
programmes.
The unions are in dispute over the introduction of performance pay and plans
for new contract terms which they say will lead to longer working days and
less time off.
