</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JERUSALEM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Former Bank Leumi chairman Ernst Japhet was found guilty of fraud yesterday,
the 10th executive convicted for a 1983 scandal that cost the government
more than Dollars 9bn, Reuter reports from Jerusalem.
The Jerusalem district court sentenced the nine others to up to eight months
