official said yesterday. TAP will offer retirement packages to 39 employees
in the first phase of a wider cost-cutting programme. The company will also
study the possibility of ending service to Boston, Montreal and Toronto and
flying only to Newark. The staff reductions and possible route changes would
not go into effect before the end of the 1994 summer season, the official
said. In January the airline accepted a government bailout plan that would
inject some Dollars 1bn over the next three years. The plan is being
examined by the European Union.
