FT  13 MAY 94 / World News in Brief: Fall in US sales expected to cost
GrandMet Pounds 40m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in the international drinks and food giant Grand Metropolitan fell
26p to 457p as the group said falling demand in the US drinks market was
likely to cost it Pounds 40m this year. The group dashed hopes of immediate
disentanglement from its struggling Inntrepreneur Estates venture with
Courage. Page 19; Lex, Page 18; Saloons set for showdown, Page 21; London
stocks, Page 38
