<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 94 / Khmer Rouge releases hostages
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PHNOM PENH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ms Melissa Himes, an American aid worker, and two Cambodian colleagues, held
hostage for 42 days by Khmer Rouge guerrillas were released unharmed
yesterday, aid officials said, Reuter reports from Phnom Penh.
'They are now free  - that is the news we got this afternoon,' said an
official from the relief agency, Food for the Hungry International. Ms
Himes, 24, an FHI development worker, was reported missing on March 31 after
she went to retrieve a vehicle in southern Kampot province.
</TEXT>
