<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 94 / London Stock Exchange: Kingfisher upset
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in high street retailer Kingfisher fell sharply as rumours circulated
of a large derivatives trade, said to have been undertaken by Swiss Bank,
and possibly linked to a potentially large sale of Kingfisher shares next
month.
The possibility of a sale arises because, according to dealers, one third of
the 68m Kingfisher shares used last year to purchase Darty, the French
electrical retailer, can be sold by the holders from June 3.
However, stores analysts said the chances of the French institutions that
are among the holders of the shares - which include the company's family and
workforce, as well as some institutional investors - all deciding to sell
the stock at the same time must be highly unlikely. But the Swiss Bank story
unnerved the stock, which ended 17 off at 572p, albeit in modest trade of
2.4m.
</TEXT>
