<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 94 / International Capital Markets: New Philadelphia market
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Philadelphia Stock Exchange yesterday announced it is forming a new
market that will allow investors to customise currency options contracts to
their particular needs.
The PHILX, the world's busiest exchange-based market for currency options,
is hoping that its new forum - called the United Currency Options Market -
will bridge the gap between listed currency options markets and the much
larger over-the-counter options market.
The bulk of the currency options business is conducted away from exchanges
where banks and securities firms design contracts to customers'
specifications. The UCOM is the PHILX's attempt to win some of that business
from the over-the-counter market.
The PHILX described the UCOM as a 'flexible trading environment' that will
allow users to employ tailor-made trading and hedging tools in a regulated
environment.
</TEXT>
