   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
America Online, a fast-growing US provider of telecommunications-based
information services, announced yesterday that it was buying Redgate
Communications, a privately-owned multimedia services company, for around
Dollars 28m in stock.
Mr Steve Case, president of America Online, said modem-based on-line
services and CD-Rom based multimedia were both growing rapidly, but so far
they had been separate. As a result, on-line services were unexciting and
CD-Rom titles were not connected to a telecommunications network.
'The combination of America Online and Redgate enables us to create hybrid
offerings that marry the best attributes of each,' he added.
Redgate is based in Vero Beach, Florida, employs around 100 and had 1993
revenues of around Dollars 13m. Its shareholders will receive 444,184 shares
of America Online stock, which closed last night at Dollars 64, down Dollars
1/2 .
