FT  12 MAY 94 / Letters to the Editor: Salary of new IoD chief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr MICHAEL MANDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Your statement that the new IoD director-general's salary is to
increase from Peter Morgan's Pounds 148,000 to Pounds 180,000 ('Nationwide
chief to head IoD', May 5) is not correct.
The present director-general receives a salary of Pounds 148,000, plus a
pension contribution of Pounds 30,000 - a total remuneration package of
Pounds 178,000.
The new director-general will receive a salary of Pounds 160,000 and a
pension contribution of approximately Pounds 20,000 - a total remuneration
package of Pounds 180,000, and this salary will be frozen for three years.
Michael Mander,
chairman,
Institute of Directors,
116 Pall Mall,
London SW1Y 5ED
