<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 94 / Arts: New boost for Arts Council
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The director Trevor Nunn and architect Sir Richard Rogers are to take up key
roles in the Arts Council under new chairman Lord Gowrie. The appointments,
announced yesterday by the Heritage Secretary Peter Brooke, are seen as part
of a move to restore the council's damaged reputation. Following abortive
attempts to restructure London's orchestras last year, there were widespread
calls for the abolition of the Arts Council.
</TEXT>
