FT  12 MAY 94 / Employers call for industrial strategy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART, Labour Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain lacks a long-term agenda to develop technology and industry, and the
Treasury is taking too complacent a view of recovery, the Engineering
Employers Federation said yesterday.
A federation report, published before the government's white paper on
competitiveness which is due on Monday, says the trade deficit and the
consumption/investment imbalance will not be solved merely by recovery.
Mr Graham MacKenzie, federation director-general, said: 'There is an urgent
need for strategic decisions.'
Manufacturing is receiving good support from the government, the report
says, but it is critical of the lack of strategy for energy and transport
infrastructures.
