<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 94 / Water cut-offs fall by a third
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The number of homes in England and Wales that had water supplies
disconnected for not paying bills fell by a third to 12,452 in the 12 months
to the end of March 31, from 18,636 in the previous period, water watchdog
Ofwat said.
This compares with 21,282 in the peak period for disconnections, the 12
months to March 1992, which lead to widespread criticism of the privatised
water companies.
Mr Ian Byatt, Ofwat director-general, said: 'Companies have responded well
to my guidelines on handling debt sensitively and avoiding disconnections.
Companies are improving their approach.'
