<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 94 / IMF approves Romanian loan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIRGINIA MARSH
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUCHAREST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The International Monetary Fund yesterday approved a 19-month loan agreement
for Romania worth Dollars 700m (Pounds 479.4m), its first new loan to the
country in nearly two years. Under the deal, Romania has agreed to bring
annual inflation down to two digits by the end of the year from the present
265 per cent, to speed up privatisation and restructuring of the state
sector, which still accounts for more than 90 per cent of industry, and to
maintain internal convertibility of the leu, the national currency. IMF
approval of the loan package, agreed in principle last December, was delayed
due to the government's slowness in drafting new tax laws and its 1994
budget.
